    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says (observation) to what it means — discerning the author's theological intent within the canonical context of Kings, the Deuteronomistic History, and the larger prophetic tradition. The movements below trace the chapter's argument through four pericopes, giving sustained attention to the hardest exegetical problem in the chapter (3:27) and to the canonical pattern the chapter establishes for reading the Elisha cycle.",
